hunt down
Homonym Number:
Word Class: verb
Sense Number:
Definition:[high country farming] [see hunt back] to move sheep from the tops or basins to a lower area [for tupping or when snow threatens.]


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date:  28/10/1933
Source:  Press, The  (Acland Glossary)
Author:
Vol / Page:  17
Edition:
Quote:  Hunt down, to hunt the sheep off the higher parts of their winter country on to lower, safer spurs when snow is expected. e.g. 'We hunted down every day for a week but no snow came.'
